The paper discusses a successful attack on a statistical queries system, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The attack involves using linear programming and statistical analysis, which are techniques commonly used in database systems (cs.DB) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also evaluates the effectiveness of the algorithm with various dataset sizes and error rates, which falls under the category of data science (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT).
